==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Albite
<hw>Al"bite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>albus</ets>
white.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of the feldspar family,
triclinic in crystallization, and in composition a silicate of alumina
and soda. It is a common constituent of granite and of various igneous
rocks. See <er>Feldspar</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>albizzia</ent>⟦br⟧
